On Tue, 23 Apr 2002, pacbell wrote:

> <Close up all of the heater system - you are loosing cooling air to the 
> <outside air. You can overheat your bus this way.
> 
> Are you talking about the hoses from the electic fan to  the heating system?

yes

> What about the heating system under the bus? If it is not hooked up to the ducting, should it be blocked off?

nah, that is "after engine cooling air" so as long as it isn't blocking
the flow of air it is harmless if it leaks, of course you won't get much
heat up front either

 I totally removed the heating system from my 78, and blocked off the air
ducts on the cooling input side.  still runs cool, actually a little
cooler than before but very unscientific since other things were done

